 new users from 26.04 won't have \\\"open in termal\\\" working out-of-the-box.\\r\\n\\r\\nSo basic options were to either switch to ptyxis now or somehow detect Ubuntu 25.10+, when it was added. Both have significant downsides - there are still a lot of users on 24.04 and other distros and hardcoding logic seems fragile.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs a general solution, I thought we can just consider all supported terminals, when trying to figure what's to use as the default for the current user.\\r\\nSo I moved `defaultTerminalForPlatform` from frontend to backend so we can run `which` on all terminals we do support and subsequnetly `allTerminalOptions` now also comes from Rust. Tested - works fine, no errors.\\r\\nOne special case in `get_recommended_terminal_for_platform` - we don't check anything using `which` and just use `terminal`, as it's generally available on every Mac and is the system default there.\\r\\n\",\"deletions\":106,\"files\":[{\"path\":\"apps/desktop/README.md\",\"additions\":11,\"deletions\":5},{\"path\":\"apps/desktop/src/components/settings/GeneralSettings.svelte\",\"additions\":18,\"deletions\":32},{\"path\":\"apps/desktop/src/lib/bootstrap/deps.ts\",\"additions\":3,\"deletions\":0},{\"path\":\"apps/desktop/src/lib/settings/terminalService.ts\",\"additions\":21,\"deletions\":0},{\"path\":\"apps/desktop/src/lib/state/initUserSettings.test.ts\",\"additions\":73,\"deletions\":33},{\"path\":\"apps/desktop/src/lib/state/uiState.svelte.ts\",\"additions\":17,\"deletions\":16},{\"path\":\"apps/desktop/src/routes/+layout.svelte\",\"additions\":4,\"deletions\":2},{\"path\":\"crates/but-api/Cargo.toml\",\"additions\":1,\"deletions\":2},{\"path\":\"crates/but-api/src/legacy/mod.rs\",\"additions\":0,\"deletions\":1},{\"path\":\"crates/but-api/src/lib.rs\",\"additions\":2,\"deletions\":0},{\"path\":\"crates/but-api/src/open/mod.rs\",\"additions\":23,\"deletions\":5},{\"path\":\"crates/but-api/src/open/terminal.rs\",\"additions\":113,\"deletions\":0},{\"path\":\"crates/